  "Summary": "This bill would permit the Department of Transportation, Department of Sanitation (“DSNY”), and any Department designated by DSNY to place a sticker, no larger than 8.5x11 inches, on the window of any motor vehicle as a method of enforcing alternate side parking rules.",
  "TextID": 83219,
  "Text": "Be it enacted by the Council as follows:\n      \n      \n      Section 1. Section 19-163.2 of the administrative code of the city of New York, as added by local law number 20 for the year 2012, is amended to read as follows:\n      � 19-163.2 [Limitation on the use] Use of adhesive stickers in the enforcement of alternate side of the street parking rules. [Neither the] The department [nor], the department of sanitation, [shall] and any other department designated by the department of sanitation may affix an adhesive sticker to [any] a window of a motor vehicle [solely in connection with] to advise the operator of such vehicle of the [enforcement] violation by such operator of alternate side of the street parking rules. The dimension of any such sticker shall not exceed eight and one-half inches by 11 inches.\n      � 2. This local law takes effect immediately.\n\n\nNAW/MBB\nLS #19711\nInt. #1334-2025\n06/18/2026 3:20 PM\n\n\n      1\n      \n      \n      1",
